Inheritance

- A Java Property Wherein, the "subclass" inherits the
  fields and methods of the "superclass".

- "extends" Keyword must be used.

Terminology
* If Student inherits the property of Person, then

- Student "extends" Person
- Student is a "subclass" of Person
- Person is a "superclass" of Person
- Person is the PARENT class
- Student is the CHILD class
- Person is the "base" class
- Student is the "derived" class